---
import AboutLayout from '../layouts/AboutLayout.astro';
import AboutPhotoBubble from '../components/AboutPhotoBubble.astro';

// Server-side fallback for SEO / no-JS users
const start = new Date('2023-01-01T00:00:00');
const now = new Date();
let years = now.getFullYear() - start.getFullYear();
const monthDiff = now.getMonth() - start.getMonth();
const dayDiff = now.getDate() - start.getDate();
if (monthDiff < 0 || (monthDiff === 0 && dayDiff < 0)) years--;
if (years < 0) years = 0;
const yearsLabel = `${years} year${years === 1 ? '' : 's'}`;
---

<AboutLayout
  title="About Me"
  description="Civil engineering PhD, systems builder, and data-driven life logger."
  pubDate="2025-10-14"
  wide={true}
  showViews={false}
>

  <!-- 🗨️ Little José hero -->
  <AboutPhotoBubble
    slot="hero"
    src="/images/about-lifeloggerz.gif"
    alt="Family gathered while young José draws at the table."
    bubbleText="Déjenme terminar esto..."
    hotspotBottom="8%"
    hotspotLeft="27%"
    hotspotWidth="24%"
    hotspotHeight="32%"
    bubbleBottom="40%"
    bubbleLeft="45%"
  />

  <div class="about">
    <p>
      I’m <strong>José</strong>, the kid sitting with a pen and paper in the photo above. I’m an engineering grad student and the person behind <strong>LifeLoggerz</strong>.
      This is where I turn messy routines into repeatable systems using <strong>Google Sheets dashboards, Python tools, and simple workflows</strong> that make research and daily life run smoother.
    </p>

    <h2>🎓 How Did This All Start?</h2>
    <p>
      You can explore the <strong>2023, 2024, and 2025 raw data sheets</strong> to see how these systems evolved.
      I had <strong>no prior experience with Excel or Google Sheets</strong>, so I learned one formula at a time, then moved into formatting and automation with Apps Script and APIs.
      Today, logging my essential stats takes about <strong>5 minutes</strong>, though my diary entries take longer.
      No matter how tired I am, <strong>I still log it.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>📊 LifeLoggerz Philosophy</h2>
    <p>
      Small habits compound. I started by tracking sleep and meals. Now I track <strong>over 150 variables</strong>:
      sleep, food, health, work, study, music, books, even “blunders.”
      Over time, this became a personal operating system. <strong>I use it to make decisions based on data.</strong>
      LifeLoggerz shares the templates and code so you can take what works and <strong>build your own system.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>🛠 Tools & Systems I Share</h2>
    <ul class="centered-list">
      <li>Google Sheets templates and dashboards for daily life and research</li>
      <li>Python apps for analysis, visualization, and exports (Excel and PowerPoint)</li>
      <li>Templates and routines that remove decision fatigue</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🎸 What Do I Do With the Time Gained?</h2>
    <p>
      For a while, this was my only hobby. <strong>Nothing else mattered.</strong> Every spare minute went into improving these systems.
      Eventually, I hit diminishing returns. There is a limit to how much you should track, and I reached it around May 2025.
      My systems did not need constant upgrading, so I stepped back.
    </p>

    <p>
      Now I keep things stable and use the time I gained. I practice flamenco guitar, listen to audiobooks while I drive or do chores,
      run, learn languages, and spend time with family.
      Optimization created the space. <strong>Now I actually use it.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>🌱 Why This Blog Exists</h2>
    <p>
      For the past <span id="years-since" data-start="2023-01-01">{yearsLabel}</span>, I have been showing these systems to people.
      This site makes them easy to explore and use.
      If you are curious about tracking your habits, streamlining research, or building your own life system, you are in the right place.
    </p>

    <h2>📬 Get in Touch</h2>
    <p class="centered-email">
      Have a question or suggestion about a template or script?<br />
      Tell me what you are building or what you would like to see next. I would love to hear from you.
      <br /><br />
      📧 <strong>lifeloggerz.official@gmail.com</strong>
    </p>
  </div>

  <style is:global>
    .about h2 {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .centered-list {
      list-style-position: inside;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }

    .centered-list li {
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
    }

    .centered-email {
      text-align: center;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    (function () {
      const el = document.getElementById('years-since');
      if (!el) return;
      const startStr = el.dataset.start || '2023-01-01';
      const start = new Date(startStr + 'T00:00:00');
      const now = new Date();
      let y = now.getFullYear() - start.getFullYear();
      const m = now.getMonth() - start.getMonth();
      const d = now.getDate() - start.getDate();
      if (m < 0 || (m === 0 && d < 0)) y--;
      if (y < 0) y = 0;
      el.textContent = `${y} year${y === 1 ? '' : 's'}`;
    })();
  </script>
</AboutLayout>
